  "category": "Uncategorized",
  "description": "Add Explicit Close Button to Lightbox Image Preview\n\nImplement a visible and accessible close/exit button for the lightbox image preview component to improve user experience and discoverability.\n\nRequirements:\n- Add a clearly visible close button (typically an \"X\" icon) to the lightbox overlay\n- Position the button in a standard location (top-right corner is conventional)\n- Ensure the button is visible against all image backgrounds (use contrasting color or semi-transparent background)\n- Make the button easily clickable/tappable with appropriate touch target size (minimum 44x44px)\n- Maintain existing close functionality (ESC key, clicking overlay background) as fallback options\n- Add hover/focus states for better interactivity feedback\n- Ensure close button is keyboard accessible and properly announced to screen readers\n- Test across different viewport sizes to ensure button remains accessible on mobile devices",
